-- Rostelecom to Gain 100% in Pay TV Operator NTK, Kommersant Says
-- B y   I l y a   K h r e n n i k o v
-- 2012-02-17T04:04:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-17/rostelecom-to-gain-100-in-pay-tv-operator-ntk-kommersant-says.html
OAO Rostelecom,  Russia ’s dominant
fixed-line phone operator, plans to boost its stake in pay
television operator National Telecommunications, or NTK, to 100
percent,  Kommersant  reported.  Rostelecom may spend 13.8 billion rubles ($460 million) to
acquire the 28 percent of NTK shares it doesn’t already own from
OAO Gazprombank, the Moscow-based daily said, citing
unidentified people.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ilya Khrennikov in Moscow at 
 ikhrennikov@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
